{
  "text": "Adoptive Transfer Experiments. Cell suspensions obtained from lymph nodes from TNCB-sensitized wt mice were injected into the ears of naive STAT6 \u03ea/\u03ea mice or wt mice (five mice per group; 2 \u03eb 10 5 per 20 l PBS [CITATION_1] ). The mice were immediately challenged by applying 10 l 1% TNCB in olive oil or olive oil alone on both sides of the ear. In these experiments, negative controls were groups of mice injected with PBS subcutaneously into the ear and challenged with 1% TNCB, or groups of mice injected with lymph node cells subcutaneously into the ear and challenged with olive oil. Ear thickness was measured as described above after 24 h. ",
  "correct_citation": {
